svg.text: Hi there. Botspot here - developer of WoR-Flasher.​The Windows on Raspberry project seems to be dying. Wi-Fi still does not work,​the Pi500, CM5, and Pi5 16GB won't boot it, and many of the devs have left.​​I started a new project to solve these issues.​It's called BVM, and it runs Windows in a virtual machine on Pi OS.​Wi-Fi works, audio playback works, everything that works on WoR works,​and you can pass-through USB devices for Windows to directly use.​As a bonus, you can use Raspberry Pi OS on the outside at the same time.​Or any ARM Linux really.​BVM often runs faster than WoR because it deletes Windows bloatware and ads.​​Note:​If you still want to proceed with WoR-Flasher and use a Pi4, you need to choose​an older Windows 11 version: 22631.2861. Newer versions don't boot on Pi4.​Thanks for reading! :-)
